location: Hudson Valley, Hudson Valley, New York
postcontent: Blueprinted Remington 700 chambered in a 6.5 the inner tenon was opened up .010" and new threads were single point cut center to bore. The actions lugs have also been squared and trued. The bolt lugs, as well as the bolt nose and face have been trued and squared. All machine work is done on a precision lathe with a single point cuter all center to bore. Both the action and bolt are dial indicated to .0001" before any work is performed. For this build we used a Shilen match grade chrome barrel with a 1-8 twist rate. The contour is a "Sendero" contour which is a light bull barrel. The barrel threads were also single point cut and hand fit to this action. The breech was cut to .0035" and the headspace was cut to .0015". This is much tighter than factory specs and will lead to a much more accurate shooter. The barrel was crowned with an 11 degree target crown. I have plenty of pics to share, detachable mag; ect. Rifle is being offered with an HS precision "sendero" stock with a BDL trigger guard and the factory trigger adjusted to a crsip 3lbs. with zero creep. This rifle will easily shoot 1/2 MOA with factory ammo and is capable of 1/4 MOA using hand loaded ammo.

title: For Sale:  RSSE - The Ruger Engraved Single Six. Rarest of all!
location: Fort Myers, South West Florida, Florida
postcontent: This is the Holy Grail of all Ruger firearms, and one of the fastest appreciating $$$value$$$ firearms in the world. In the mid-1950’s during the first years of production of the Single Six line, Bill Ruger himself started a program to create a beautiful fully-engraved keepsake Single Six pistol; a pistol ..."carefully chosen to represent the very best tradional style in this gun-makers art". This may be the first time a major American firearms company offered a special catalog line of fully engraved pistols making them instantly collectable. In the end only 261 Single Six Factory Engraved Models were ever produced, making them some of the rarest Rugers on the planet. These beautiful pistols were lavishly engraved by Charles H. Jarred (Jerred's personal initial monogram is located on top of the barrel near the front sight and is clearly visible - see picture 4.) They are considered by knowledgeable collectors to be the most desirable of the entire Single Action line of Ruger handguns. This offering features what experts refer to as the "Standard Pattern Embellishment" - the traditional hand-cut floral engraving pattern Bill Ruger chose to be the signature engraving imagery on the two tone pistol, which also included fancy premium select walnut wood grips. They are known as Ruger Cat. No. RSSE Factory Engraved - serial number 4494x, 22LR with 5 1/2" barrel. Our pistol also includes the original "Golden Eagle" black mongrammed leatherette presentation display box it came in which features the famous green felt lining complete with all metal appointments and working double latches - this rare box alone is worth $1000 as many were lost or damaged. Seemingly unfired in perfect 97-98% minty condition with only the usual slight cylinder turn line and very minor finish fade on the loading gate mound, muzzle edge and extractor housing tip - all common wear more than likely from sitting undisturbed for decades and rubbing gently inside the felt lined box. They are almost never encountered in better overall condition than this. It's outstanding. No Ruger collection is complete without this one. Don't miss this unique opportunity to own one of the rarest and most desirable firearms in the world. It's an American original that will never be seen again. And being nearly 60 years old, of course it is C&R eligible. WHAT YOU SEE is that which you will receive. Please ask all questions you may have before bidding. All Sales are final. Buyer MUST send an FFL/C&R, it is required to complete the sale. No sales to CA, NY, MA, NJ, CT or where prohibited to own. Shipping with or without insurance will be determined by the buyer. (Standard USPS Priority mail non-insured is approx. $25. USPS Priority Mail insured up to a maximum of $5000 will be approximately $86. Fedex or UPS 2nd day insured up to $5000 will be approx. $120.) There will be an extra $50 charge on top of everything if your FFL dealer insists on having my 01 FFL dealer send it to him - rather than receiving it from me directly. Good luck.

title: For Sale:  Cane Gun - 38 Special
postcontent:
A cane gun is a walking cane with a hidden gun built into it. Cane guns are often referred to as "poacher's guns", but were far out of the price range of common poachers, and were commonly carried by gentlemen to use on wild game of opportunity.[1] Cane guns now are very rare to find and are mostly in the hands of private collectors and museums. Cane guns are usually fitted to fire large handgun type cartridges which is perfect for low pressure conditions of normal guns and excel in the high pressure conditions of a cane gun, with each cane gun holding a single cartridge, usually a high power type.

This is a full size real cane containing a gun barrel in the cane and a firing mechanism  near the handle. It fires a 38 Special.  It is a sneaky and devastating weapon.

It is in new condition.

Very seldom will you ever get a chance to own such a unique weapon. For the collector who wants to add something unique and unusual to his or her collection, this is the perfect choice.

This is a class 3 weapon and requires going thru a class 3 firearms dealer to transfer it.
